        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 2:45PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 244 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Villa Verde, or over Weslaco, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Donna Public Library, Adams Gardens, Weslaco Mid Valley Airport, Lion
Lake, A.p. Solis Middle School, Llano Grande Country Club, Beatriz
Garza Middle School, Weslaco City Hall, North Bridge Elementary
School, and Taylor Elementary School.

This includes US Highway 281 between mile markers 800 and 812.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
